<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-237-691  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 237 691.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Jan 2 1989 v216 n1 p12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cerritos: a testing ground for telecom's future. (Cerritos,California)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dortch, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The homes and businesses of Cerritos, CA will soon be taking partin a GTE Corp study of advanced communication services.andP;  MainStreet, a videotex service, will be one of the first servicestested by GTE Services.andP;  Subscribers will be able to view andpurchase wares, as well as access restaurant, menu and otherinformation.andP;  Main Street will be delivered through coaxial cablevia a user interface that is controlled by a television remotecontrol device.andP;  GTE will be working with Apollo CableVision inCerritos and hopes the project will not only improve telephonecompanies' relations with cable companies but also provide crucialinformation on revenue, cost and quality.andP;  GTE also plans to testvideo-on-demand and to establish a fiber optic network forfull-motion video and video telephony experiments.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   GTE Corp. (research)Apollo CableVision (contracts).andO;Ticker:    GTE.andO;Topic:     Fiber opticsCaliforniaTelecommunicationsCoaxial cablesCable TVVideotexTeleshoppingField TestingFuture TechnologiesCommunications Service SuppliersMain Street (Videotex system).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>